d that saw the United States eclipse Britain as the globally hegemonic nation and the related inauguration of new forms of liberal economic globalization. But this is not a distant history. Cinema and the Wealth of Nations examines a foundational conjuncture in the establishment of media forms and a media system instrumental in, and structural to, the emergence and expansion of a world system that has been-and continues to be-brutally violent, unequal, and destructive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aCapitalism and mass media. 0aIndustrial filmszUnited States. 0aMotion pictures and globalization. 0aMotion pictures in propagandazUnited States. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 70(DE-601)1043396160(DE-588)4154384-1aFilmwirtschaft2gnd 70(DE-601)1047934060(DE-588)4248464-9aIndustriefilm2gnd 70(DE-601)1055239250(DE-588)4154372-5aFilmpolitik2gnd 70(DE-601)1057327100(DE-588)4126398-4aPropagandafilm2gnd 70(DE-601)1062737280(DE-588)4029577-1aKapitalismus2gnd 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520965348423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520965348.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles